xchange%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60b0d00102ac410018f934f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22694%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20markets%20have%20hit%20record%20highs%20recently%20on%20upbeat%20investor%20sentiment.%3Cp%3EEmmanuel%20Dunand%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20policies%20may%20have%20disrupted%20trade%2C%20but%20not%20global%20economic%20activity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestment%2C%20employment%2C%20and%20spending%20remain%20strong%20despite%20initial%20fears%20of%20a%20slowdown%2C%20wrote%20Goldman%20Sachs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGrowth%20forecasts%20for%20this%20year%20have%20actually%20improved%20from%20earlier%2C%20more%20pessimistic%20calls.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%3C%2Fa%3E%20new%20policies%20may%20be%20upending%20the%20global%20trade%20order%2C%20but%20so%20far%2C%20they're%20not%20hitting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeconomy%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehard%2C%20wrote%20Goldman%20Sachs%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20very%20few%20signs%20that%20uncertainty%20is%20taking%20a%20toll%20on%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20analysts%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20wrote%20in%20a%20Thursday%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20analysts%20had%20expected%20Trump's%20second%20term%20to%20slow%20economic%20activity%2C%20the%20numbers%20tell%20a%20different%20story.%20Since%20late%202024%2C%20investment%2C%20factory%20hiring%2C%20consumer%20spending%2C%20and%20broader%20economic%20activity%20have%20all%20stayed%20resilient%20across%20major%20developed%20and%20emerging%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20growth%20forecasts%20for%20both%20the%20second%20quarter%20and%20this%20full%20year%20have%20actually%20improved%20from%20earlier%2C%20more%20pessimistic%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20pointed%20out%20that%20in%20most%20economies%2C%20trade-exposed%20investment%20accounts%20for%20a%20small%20share%20of%20GDP%2C%20so%20the%20impact%20may%20just%20be%20%26quot%3Btoo%20small%20to%20see.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20factory%20investment%2C%20especially%20in%20emerging%20markets%2C%20has%20dipped%2C%20but%20this%20accounts%20for%20just%200.2%20to%200.3%20percentage%20points%20of%20GDP%20in%20major%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20also%20wrote%20that%20uncertainty%20usually%20bites%20hardest%20when%20financial%20conditions%20tighten.%20But%20global%20liquidity%20has%20actually%20improved%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20businesses%20to%20borrow%20money%20and%20invest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20activity%20and%20investment%20expectations%20that%20dipped%20in%20April%20%E2%80%94%20which%20coincided%20with%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-liberation-day-reciprocal-tariffs-speech-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20announcement%20%E2%80%94%20have%20already%20bounced%20back%20on%20improved%20tariff%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20such%2C%20while%20we%20continue%20to%20expect%20that%20tariffs%20will%20slow%20activity%20later%20this%20year%2C%20we%20expect%20this%20will%20be%20mostly%20driven%20by%20the%20direct%20impacts%20of%20tariffs%20rather%20than%20uncertainty%20around%20trade%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman's%20report%20came%20as%20the%20US%20posted%20better-than-expected%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjune-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-employment-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployment%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June.%20The%20economy%20added%20147%2C000%20jobs%2C%20and%20unemployment%20fell%20f