trong%3ESustainable%20Livelihood%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Promoting%20geranium%20farming%20could%20help%20farmers%20%3Cstrong%3Eincrease%20income%20and%20financial%20stability%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeranium%20was%20first%20introduced%20in%20the%20temperate%20regions%20of%20South%20India%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Nilgiris%20(Tamil%20Nadu)%2C%20parts%20of%20Karnataka%2C%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20due%20to%20their%20suitable%20climate.%20A%20medicinal%20and%20aromatic%20plant%2C%20it%20is%20not%20eaten%20by%20animals%20and%20rarely%20attacked%20by%20pests.%20Its%20leaves%20start%20to%20grow%20shortly%20after%20harvest%2C%20and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F403491%2Fharyana-techie-and-wife-launch-successful-morina-business-organic-farming-improving-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20farmers%20can%20easily%20earn%20more%20profit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeranium%20is%20valued%20for%20its%20leaves%2C%20which%20are%20processed%20to%20extract%20essential%20oil.%20This%20oil%20is%20in%20high%20demand%20both%20in%20India%20and%20internationally.%20Once%20planted%2C%20geranium%20can%20be%20harvested%20four%20times%20a%20year%20for%20about%20four%20years%2C%20yielding%2015%E2%80%9316%20tons%20of%20leaves%20every%20three%20months.%20Geranium%20plants%20require%20less%20irrigation%20making%20them%20a%20practical%20alternative%20to%20traditional%20crops%20like%20paddy%20and%20pulses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20870px)%20100vw%2C%20870px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FThe-Patade-family-1_10_11zon-1751287674.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22870%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Geranium%20farming%20in%20Chhattisgarh%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FThe-Patade-family-1_10_11zon-17